<TITLE> Anam elected BCB senior vice president </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Nov 26 (bdnews24.com)  Mahbub Anam has been elected senior vice president of the Bangladesh Cricket Board, while Ahmed Sajjadul Alam Bobby and Asaduzzaman Khashru were elected vice presidents unopposed on Wednesday. The board declared Anam the winner, but did not reveal the number of votes he received. Enayet Hossain Siraj contested against Anam, who was elected director from category B for Dhaka clubs. Bobby came from Categories B and C comprised of Dhaka clubs, former cricketers, educational boards, etc, while Khashru was elected from Category C for district and divisional associations. The newly elected BCB directors chose secret ballots to elect their senior vice president after a meeting at Sher-e-Bangla National Stadium on Wednesday. The meeting also formed a five-member committee, which will propose the chiefs of the different sub-committees ahead of the second executive committee meeting on Dec 2. As many as 23 directors were elected in three categories in the Nov 12 election while president Major General Sina Ibe Jamali and director Firoz Ahmed were chosen by the government and the National Sports Council in the 25-member executive body of the country's most affluent board. bdn
